HEADWORD: Gastroduodenitis
<hw>Gas`tro*du`o*de*ni"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.
See <er>Gastroduodenal</er>, and <er>-itis</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Inflammation of the stomach and duodenum. It is
one of the most frequent causes of jaundice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

